    "body":  "# The Civic Desk v0.3.2 release candidate notes\n\nWindows-only public beta release candidate. The current Windows installer asset was built from product commit `c1239fda79dd3bfc58e24c52657997550ccd2930`.\n\nNote: the `v0.3.2` tag itself points at an earlier release-line commit and is not being moved during this no-tag release loop; use the installer hash below as the public asset identity.\n\nInstaller asset:\n- `The.Civic.Desk_0.3.2_x64-setup.exe`\n- SHA256: `A8E32A95AE64C69B3A58B0A5CC670F04B6ADCA726933CAA49C5CC4AEBD3D37B1`\n- Size: `5251952` bytes\n\nChecksum asset:\n- `SHA256SUMS.txt`\n- Contains `A8E32A95AE64C69B3A58B0A5CC670F04B6ADCA726933CAA49C5CC4AEBD3D37B1  The.Civic.Desk_0.3.2_x64-setup.exe`\n\nWhy this rebuild exists:\n- The prior cleanroom rerun found the installed WebView onboarding form could not be driven reliably through the tester channel after Step 1, even though the app launched and visibility checks passed.\n- This build moves Step 1 to the same fixed bottom action bar used by the rest of onboarding and makes starter profiles one-click continue actions through the normal identity persistence path, so installed-app cleanroom testing does not depend on a clipped header button or fragile field coordinates.\n- It retains the previous shared public-text quality normalization and legacy database remediation for malformed calendar/listing leads and drafts.\n\nLocal verification passed:\n- `npm test -- --run`: 226 passed\n- `cargo test --all --locked --quiet`: 236 passed, 0 ignored\n- `cargo clippy --all-targets --locked -- -D warnings`: passed\n- `npm run build`: passed\n- `npm run tauri -- build`: passed\n- Windows installer smoke: `.agent-runs/windows-installer-smoke-20260704-202313/windows-installer-smoke-receipt.json`\n- Packaged first-run walkthrough: `.agent-runs/packaged-first-run-walkthrough-20260704-202346/packaged-first-run-walkthrough-receipt.json`\n- Stable release smoke with full source-import fixtures: `.agent-runs/release-smoke-20260704-203012/release-smoke-receipt.json`\n\nRelease scope:\n- Windows only is the tested public-beta installer path.\n- Installer is unsigned; SmartScreen warning is expected. Users should verify SHA256, click More info, then Run anyway.\n- macOS and Linux installers remain backlog/proof-needed.\n- Final cleanroom rerun is still required before this release candidate is called beta-release ready."
